result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer L Vanderboom was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-False Representation <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(d).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine to be paid at $100.00 per month commencing 06/01/2016 and each month thereafter or penalty of 8 days jail for non-payment.

records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Jennifer L Vanderboom in court with Attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Kevin Michael Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files an amended information.  Defendant entered a guilty plea to Count #1 on amended information.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1 on amended information.  State gives sentencing recommendation.  State states that Defendant has paid restitution in full.  Attorney Fragoso makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements. Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  FINE:  $389.00 - to be paid at $100.00 per month, commencing 6/1/16, alternate 8 days jail if not paid.

Defendant Jennifer L Vanderboom in court with Attorney Jorge R Fragoso.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Natalie Schiferl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Fragoso requests an adjournment as he just received a response from the state yesterday as to counter offer and Defendant needs additional time to pay restitution.  State does not object to adjournment request.  Court denies request and leaves case on for jury trial on Tuesday, 4/26/16.  Attorney Fragoso requests an additional jury status date on 4/25/16.  Bail remains as fixed.  Jury status hearing scheduled for April 25, 2016 at 08:30 am.
Filed by the State. Witness list attached.

Defendant Jennifer L Vanderboom in court with Attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Fragoso requests a jury status and jury trial date.  Court adjourns.   Bail remains as fixed.  Jury status hearing scheduled for April 21, 2016 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial - 12 person scheduled for April 26, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jennifer L Vanderboom in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Atty Fragoso requests another date about 60 days out to review discovery and restitution.   Bail remains as fixed.  Hearing scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 10:00 am.
Defendant waives his/her right to a Preliminary Hearing.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant to have no contact with victim/witness listed in the Criminal Complaint.

Defendant Jennifer L Vanderboom in court with attorney Jorge R Fragoso.  Melissa Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  Hearing scheduled for December 4, 2015 at 10:30 am.
